metadata.documentation: AWS Greengrass seamlessly extends AWS onto physical devices so they can act locally on the data they generate, while still using the cloud for management, analytics, and durable storage. AWS Greengrass ensures your devices can respond quickly to local events and operate with intermittent connectivity. AWS Greengrass minimizes the cost of transmitting data to the cloud by allowing you to author AWS Lambda functions that execute locally.

AssociateRoleToGroup.documentation: Associates a role with a group. The role will be used by the AWS Greengrass core in order to access AWS cloud services. The role's permissions will allow Greengrass core Lambda functions to perform actions against the cloud.

AssociateServiceRoleToAccount.documentation: Associates a role which is used by AWS Greengrass. AWS Greengrass uses the role to access your Lambda functions and AWS IoT resources. This is necessary for deployments to succeed. It needs to have minimum permissions in policy ``AWSGreengrassResourceAccessRolePolicy``

CreateCoreDefinition.documentation: Creates a core definition. You may optionally provide the initial version of the core definition or use ''CreateCoreDefinitionVersion'' at a later time. AWS Greengrass Groups must each contain exactly 1 AWS Greengrass Core.

input.documentation: Information on the core definition request

CreateCoreDefinitionVersion.documentation: Creates a version of a core definition that has already been defined. AWS Greengrass Groups must each contain exactly 1 AWS Greengrass Core.

CreateDeviceDefinition.documentation: Creates a device definition. You may optinally provide the initial version of the device definition or use ``CreateDeviceDefinitionVersion`` at a later time.

CreateDeviceDefinitionVersion.documentation: Creates a version of a device definition that has already been defined.

CreateFunctionDefinition.documentation: Creates a Lambda function definition which contains a list of Lambda functions and their configurations to be used in a group. You can create an initial version of the definition by providing a list of Lambda functions and their configurations now, or use ``CreateFunctionDefinitionVersion`` later.

CreateFunctionDefinitionVersion.documentation: Create a version of a Lambda function definition that has already been defined.

CreateGroup.documentation: Creates a group. You may optionally provide the initial version of the group or use ''CreateGroupVersion'' at a later time.

CreateGroupCertificateAuthority.documentation: Creates a CA for the group. If a CA already exists, it will rotate the existing CA.

exceptions.documentation: The server encountered an unexpected error.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the new active CA ARN

CreateGroupVersion.documentation: Creates a version of a group which has already been defined.

returnType.documentation: the requested version of the Group

CreateLoggerDefinition.documentation: Creates a logger definition. You may optionally provide the initial version of the logger definition or use ``CreateLoggerDefinitionVersion`` at a later time.

CreateLoggerDefinitionVersion.documentation: Creates a version of a logger definition that has already been defined.

CreateSubscriptionDefinition.documentation: Creates a subscription definition. You may optionally provide the initial version of the subscription definition or use ``CreateSubscriptionDefinitionVersion`` at a later time.

CreateSubscriptionDefinitionVersion.documentation: Creates a version of a subscription definition which has already been defined.

DeleteCoreDefinition.documentation: Deletes a core definition. The core definition must not have been used in a deployment.

DeleteDeviceDefinition.documentation: Deletes a device definition. The device definition must not have been used in a deployment.

DeleteFunctionDefinition.documentation: Deletes a Lambda function definition. The Lambda function definition must not have been used in a deployment.

DeleteGroup.documentation: Deletes a group. The group must not have been used in deployment.

DeleteLoggerDefinition.documentation: Deletes a logger definition. The logger definition must not have been used in a deployment.

DeleteSubscriptionDefinition.documentation: Deletes a subscription definition. The subscription definition must not have been used in a deployment.

DisassociateRoleFromGroup.documentation: Disassociates the role from a group.

DisassociateServiceRoleFromAccount.documentation: Disassociates the service role from the account. Without a service role, deployments will not work.

GetAssociatedRole.documentation: Retrieves the role associated with a particular group.

GetConnectivityInfo.documentation: Retrieves the connectivity information for a core.

GetCoreDefinition.documentation: Retrieves information about a core definition version.

GetCoreDefinitionVersion.documentation: Retrieves information about a core definition version.

GetDeploymentStatus.documentation: Returns the status of a deployment.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the status of a deployment for a group.

GetDeviceDefinition.documentation: Retrieves information about a device definition.

GetDeviceDefinitionVersion.documentation: Retrieves information about a device definition version.

GetFunctionDefinition.documentation: Retrieves information about a Lambda function definition, such as its creation time and latest version.

GetFunctionDefinitionVersion.documentation: Retrieves information about a Lambda function definition version, such as which Lambda functions are included in the version and their configurations.

GetGroupCertificateAuthority.documentation: Retreives the CA associated with a group. Returns the public key of the CA.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the PKI Configuration

GetGroupCertificateConfiguration.documentation: Retrieves the current configuration for the CA used by the group.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the PKI Configuration

GetGroupVersion.documentation: Retrieves information about a group version.

GetLoggerDefinition.documentation: Retrieves information about a logger definition.

GetLoggerDefinitionVersion.documentation: Retrieves information about a logger definition version.

GetServiceRoleForAccount.documentation: Retrieves the service role that is attached to the account.

GetSubscriptionDefinition.documentation: Retrieves information about a subscription definition.

GetSubscriptionDefinitionVersion.documentation: Retrieves information about a subscription definition version.

ListCoreDefinitionVersions.documentation: Lists versions of a core definition.

ListCoreDefinitions.documentation: Retrieves a list of core definitions.

ListDeployments.documentation: Returns a history of deployments for the group.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the list of deployments for the given group Id

ListDeviceDefinitionVersions.documentation: Lists the versions of a device definition.

ListDeviceDefinitions.documentation: Retrieves a list of device definitions.

ListFunctionDefinitionVersions.documentation: Lists the versions of a Lambda function definition.

ListFunctionDefinitions.documentation: Retrieves a list of Lambda function definitions.

returnType.documentation: The Ids of all the Greengrass Function Definitions in this account.

ListGroupCertificateAuthorities.documentation: Retrieves the current CAs for a group.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the PKI Configuration

ListGroupVersions.documentation: List the versions of a group.

returnType.documentation: the list of versions and metadata for the given group Id

ListLoggerDefinitionVersions.documentation: Lists the versions of a logger definition.

ListLoggerDefinitions.documentation: Retrieves a list of logger definitions.

ListSubscriptionDefinitionVersions.documentation: Lists the versions of a subscription definition.

ListSubscriptionDefinitions.documentation: Retrieves a list of subscription definitions.

UpdateConnectivityInfo.documentation: Updates the connectivity information for the core. Any devices that belong to the group which has this core will receive this information in order to find the location of the core and connect to it.

UpdateGroupCertificateConfiguration.documentation: Updates the Cert expiry time for a group.

returnType.documentation: The response body contains the PKI Configuration
